proteinClass.name: COSMIC somatic mutations in cancer genes

tissueExpression.summary: Cytoplasmic expression in several tissues, most abundant in the gastrointestinal tract and lymphoid tissues.

verification.description: Antibody staining mainly consistent with RNA expression data.

cellExpression.summary: Mainly localized to the plasma membrane & cytosol. In addition localized to the focal adhesion sites.

data.cellLine: BJ hTERT+ SV40 Large T+ RasG12V

tissueExpression.summary: The gastrointestinal tract, subtypes of lymphoid cells, gall bladder and decidual cells showed strong cytoplasmic and membranous staining. Squamous epithelial cells and most cells in CNS were negative. Remaining normal tissues mainly displayed weak to moderate cytoplasmic and occasional membranous staining.
tissueExpression.validation: Mainly consistent with RNA expression data
Consistent with extensive gene/protein characterization data

image.description: Immunohistochemical staining of human tonsil shows distinct cytoplasmic positivity in cells in reaction center.

tissueExpression.summary: Most malignancies were weakly stained in the cytoplasm or negative. Several cases of malignant lymphoma, liver, stomach, pancreatic, ovarian, breast and colorectal cancers showed moderate cytoplasmic positivity.
